<div id="cheatsheet-page">

  <p>
    This is a short list of generally useful keyboard shortcuts for the aspirational computational power user. It's currently aimed at <a href="http://journalism.stanford.edu">Stanford Journalism</a> students and the software we currently installed in our lab: <a href="https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT201236">OS X 10.10+</a>, <a href="http://www.google.com/chrome/">Google Chrome</a>, and the <a href="https://atom.io/">Atom</a> and <a href="http://www.sublimetext.com/">Sublime Text</a> editors. However, all of these shortcuts map to common tasks and generally have similar equivalents in Windows and Linux.
  </p>

  <p>The shortcuts <span style="color: #C00;">highlighted in red</span> are especially important.
  </p>

<p><em>Keyboard styling adapted from <a href="https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/921159/Keyboard/page1.html">Dustin Cartwright's Apple Keyboard in CSS3 demo</a></em>
</p>

